# Module Metadata Scope

- `module.yaml` is module metadata, not documentation-only configuration.
- The file can be absent, but filling it is recommended.
- Metadata is synchronized to the `Module` object after successful sync.

# Core Field Set

- `name` (required): module name in Kebab Case, for example `echo-server`.
- `namespace`: namespace where module components are deployed.
- `subsystems`: list of module subsystems.
- `accessibility`: module availability and default bundle behavior by editions.
- `stage`: one of `Experimental`, `Preview`, `General Availability`, `Deprecated`.
- `weight`: startup order weight, default `900`.
- `exclusiveGroup`: only one module in same group can be active.
- `tags`: transformed into `Module` labels `module.deckhouse.io/<TAG>=""`.
- `descriptions`: free-form module purpose text.
- `disable`: module disable behavior settings.
- `requirements`: module start constraints.

# Full module.yaml Structure

Reference layout (all supported top-level sections):

```yaml
name: hello-world
namespace: d8-hello-world
subsystems:
  - networking
  - security
accessibility:
  editions:
    _default:
      available: true
      enabledInBundles:
        - Default
    ce:
      available: false
    ee:
      available: true
      enabledInBundles:
        - Managed
descriptions:
  en: |
    The module does something useful.
  ru: |
    Модуль делает полезную задачу.
disable:
  confirmation: true
  message: "Disabling removes module resources."
exclusiveGroup: network-stack
requirements:
  deckhouse: ">= 1.73"
  kubernetes: ">= 1.28"
  modules:
    ingress-nginx: "> 1.67.0"
    test: "> v0.22.1 !optional"
stage: General Availability
tags:
  - test
  - myTag
weight: 900
```

# Descriptions

- `descriptions.en`: English description.
- `descriptions.ru`: Russian description.
- Prefer multiline style for both locales.
- Keep EN and RU descriptions semantically equivalent.

# Disable Confirmation Rule

- If `disable.confirmation: true`, module can be disabled only when `ModuleConfig` has annotation:
  - `modules.deckhouse.io/allow-disabling=true`
- If annotation is missing, disable attempt must show warning with `disable.message`.

# Accessibility Structure

- Use nested structure:
  - `accessibility.editions._default`
  - `accessibility.editions.<edition>`
- Supported editions keys: `be`, `ce`, `ee`, `se`, `se-plus`.
- For each edition key:
  - `available` (`bool`)
  - `enabledInBundles` (`[]string`)
- Supported bundles values: `Default`, `Managed`, `Minimal`.

Example:

```yaml
accessibility:
  editions:
    _default:
      available: true
      enabledInBundles:
        - Default
        - Managed
    ce:
      available: false
    ee:
      available: true
      enabledInBundles:
        - Managed
```

# Requirements Formatting

- `requirements.deckhouse`: Deckhouse version constraint string.
- `requirements.kubernetes`: Kubernetes version constraint string.
- `requirements.modules`: constraints by module versions.
- For dependency testing, environment variables may be used:
  - `TEST_EXTENDER_DECKHOUSE_VERSION`
  - `TEST_EXTENDER_KUBERNETES_VERSION`

Example:

```yaml
name: hello-world
requirements:
  deckhouse: ">= 1.73"
  kubernetes: ">= 1.28"
  modules:
    ingress-nginx: "> 1.67.0"
    node-local-dns: ">= 0.0.0"
    test: "> v0.22.1 !optional"
```

# Optional Dependency Marker

- `!optional` is supported for module dependency constraints.
- Optional dependency means:
  - the target module can work without the related module;
  - if the related module is enabled, its version must satisfy constraint;
  - updates can be blocked until the related module matches requirements.
- Dependency behavior and constraints should follow DKP module dependencies documentation.

# Experimental Stage Rule

- If `stage: Experimental`, module must not be enabled by default.
- To allow usage, `allowExperimentalModules` must be set to `true`.

# Lifecycle Source Of Truth

- Module lifecycle status source of truth is `module.yaml.stage`.
- Deprecated README front matter field `moduleStatus` must not be used.
